com.mingweisamuel.zyra.entity

Class EntityApi

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mingweisamuel.zyra.entity.EntityApi
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class EntityApi
extends Object
implements Closeable
    API for interacting with entities. Also acts as a builder and cache for entity instances.

    MatchEntities are always cached by their match ID and duplicate instances will not be created unless the previous instance has left the cache.

    SummonerEntities are unambitiously cached by summoner ID or account ID, or both depending on what is supplied. Any summoners with matching IDs will not be duplicated unless the previous instance has left the cache. Summoners created using the getSummonerByName(com.mingweisamuel.zyra.enums.Region, java.lang.String) method are not put into any cache. This may change in the future.

        public SummonerEntity getSummoner(Region region,
                                  String summonerIdEnc,
                                  String accountIdEnc)
        Gets a summoner entity by region, summoner ID, and account ID. Will return a cached instance with matching summoner ID or account ID if found.

        Summoner ID and account ID should belong to the same summoner to prevent undefined behavior. Use getSummoner(Region, String) or getSummonerByAccountId(Region, String) for whichever field is known.
        Parameters:
        region - Summoner's region.
        summonerIdEnc - Summoner's ID.
        accountIdEnc - Summoner's account ID.

        A SummonerEntity instance.

      • getSummoner

        public SummonerEntity getSummoner(Region region,
                                  String summonerIdEnc,
                                  String accountIdEnc,
                                  String name)
        Gets a summoner entity by region, summoner ID, and a supplied summoner name (which will be normalized). Will return a cached instance with matching summoner ID or account ID if found.

        Summoner ID and account ID should belong to the same summoner to prevent undefined behavior. Use getSummoner(Region, String) or getSummonerByAccountId(Region, String) for whichever field is known.
        Parameters:
        region - Summoner's region.
        summonerIdEnc - Summoner's ID.
        accountIdEnc - Summoner's account ID.
        name - Summoner's name. Will be normalized, so capitalization and whitespace do not matter.
        Returns:
        A SummonerEntity instance.
